# Doton-OS

> **An open operating system ecosystem for anyone.**

Doton-OS is an open operating system ecosystem consisting of the
**Doton Microkernel**, **Doublers Instruction Set Architecture (ISA)**,
**LinkLoader Runtime Manager**, **Deshell (DSH)**, and the **Deson
Compiler Specification**.

Its purpose is not to replace existing operating systems, but to provide
an independent operating system ecosystem with its own specifications
that anyone may study, implement, improve, and build upon.

---

# Components

- 🖥️ Doton Microkernel
- ⚙️ Doublers ISA
- 🔗 LinkLoader
- 💻 Deshell (DSH)
- 🛠️ Deson Compiler
- 📜 Doton-OS Package License (DPL)

---

# Goals

- Create an independent operating system ecosystem.
- Encourage compatible operating system implementations.
- Preserve long-term specification compatibility.
- Allow the community to improve the specifications while preserving
  their original meaning.
- Provide an open ecosystem for learning, research, and development.

---

# Community

Anyone may:

- Read the specifications.
- Study the operating system ecosystem.
- Build compatible kernels.
- Build compatible software.
- Improve the official specifications while preserving their original
  architectural meaning.
- Create compatible extensions.

See the **Doton-OS Package License (DPL)** for complete licensing terms.

---

# Compatibility

Any implementation claiming compatibility with the official Doton-OS
ecosystem shall preserve the behavior defined by the official
specifications.

Community improvements to the documentation are encouraged, provided
they do not change the meaning or compatibility of the specifications.

